# ============================================================
# Tesla Command Center — Environment Configuration
# ============================================================
#
# This app supports two modes:
#
#   1. SELF-HOSTED  — Set TESSIE_API_KEY and TESSIE_VIN below.
#                     The dashboard works immediately, no setup screen.
#
#   2. BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) — Leave TESSIE_API_KEY and
#                     TESSIE_VIN empty. Visitors enter their own
#                     Tessie credentials on a setup screen.
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values.
# ============================================================

# --- Tessie Credentials (self-hosted mode) ---
# Get your API key at https://my.tessie.com/settings/api
# Your VIN is the 17-character Vehicle Identification Number.
TESSIE_API_KEY=
TESSIE_VIN=

# --- Google Maps API Key ---
# Required for the vehicle location map and drive replay.
# Create one at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Enable "Maps JavaScript API" and "Maps Embed API".
# For public deployments, restrict the key to your domain.
# In BYOK mode, users can optionally provide their own if this is not set.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
